</ul><h1>Seasons Change</h1><p>Days on the beach, lying on a chaise lounge, sipping a cocktail or some infused water. Spa treatments. A Michelin-star-level dinner under the stars.</p>
<p>If this all sounds tedious and boring to you, may we suggest an exciting new vacation destination:</p>
<p><strong>Your Childhood Home, in November &amp; December</strong>!</p>
<p>Experience all this thrilling trip has to offer, including:</p>
<p><strong>Nature’s Mysterious Wonder</strong></p>
<p>Watch in awe as a blizzard in Boise somehow cancels your flight from O’Hare to Atlanta!</p>
<p><strong>Marvels Of Commerce</strong></p>
<p>Smile like you’re totally fine with it when the airport barista tells you that the latte you ordered is fourteen dollars!</p>
<p><strong>A Sense of Community</strong></p>
<p>Make meaningful eye contact with the stranger sitting next to you, as a dad berates a gate attendant for a travel delay, complaining that, at this rate, he and his family will only have an hour and a half to make their connecting flight!</p>
<p><strong>Convenient Luggage</strong></p>
<p>Wheel your stylish Olympia Aerolite carry-on through the airport with ease, knowing the hard sides and TSA lock will protect all that is inside! (Additional purchase necessary.)</p>
<p><strong>Exciting Fluctuations In Space &amp; Time</strong></p>
<p>Feel the confusion as you run out of life updates to share with your parents a mere six minutes into the drive home from the airport!</p>
<p><strong>Cinematic Culinary Adventures</strong></p>
<p>Enter into a <em>Bear</em>-like environment as Thanksgiving dinner comes together in your parents’ kitchen!</p>
<p><strong>Gripping Escape-Room-Style Scenarios</strong></p>
<p>Decide whether to engage Uncle Cliff further, or simply abandon all your principles and concede his entirely offensive point just to end the conversation sooner!</p>
<p><strong>Dreamy Accommodations</strong></p>
<p>You won’t even realize how tiny your childhood bed is with all that tryptophan, sugar, and wine in your system!</p>
<p>Does this sound like a fantastic vacation? No? Well, too bad! You’re taking it anyway!</p>
<p>Book today!</p>
<p>(Because somehow, summer’s not even technically over for another day, yet prices are already ridiculous and they’ll only go up between now and the end of October.)</p>